status_added = Added: { $name }
status_deleted = Deleted: { $name }
status_delete_confirm = Delete "{ $name }"?
status_read_error = Read error: { $name }
status_export_error = Export error: { $name }
status_parse_error = Parse error: { $name }
status_utf8_decode_failed = UTF-8 decode failed
level_warning_intro_preview = This level contains known risky object combinations. Starting preview may not match how the original game behaves.
level_warning_intro_export = This level contains known risky object combinations. Exporting it may create a level that breaks the original game.
level_warning_intro_editor = This edit introduced known risky object combinations. The original game may behave unpredictably or break.
level_warning_intro_preview_low = This level contains known object issues. Starting preview may miss optional original-game behavior.
level_warning_intro_export_low = This level contains known object issues. Exporting it may disable optional original-game behavior without necessarily breaking the level.
level_warning_intro_editor_low = This edit introduced known object issues. The original game may skip optional systems or behave differently in some situations.
level_warning_section_high = High risk
level_warning_section_low = Lower impact
level_warning_badge_high = HIGH
level_warning_badge_low = LOW
level_warning_multiple_camera_system = Found { $count } "{ $name }" objects. Each CameraSystem spawns GameCamera and HUDCamera objects, while the original game later uses singular camera lookups like Camera.main, HUDCamera, GameCamera, and CameraSystem by name.
level_warning_multiple_game_camera = Found { $count } "{ $name }" objects. The original game expects a single MainCamera/GameCamera and uses singular lookups like Camera.main, FindGameObjectWithTag("MainCamera"), and GameObject.Find("GameCamera").
level_warning_multiple_hud_camera = Found { $count } "{ $name }" objects. The original game expects a single HUD camera and repeatedly uses FindGameObjectWithTag("HUDCamera") without ambiguity handling.
level_warning_multiple_world_object = Found { $count } "{ $name }" objects. LevelManager resolves a single World-tagged background object and then reads its PositionSerializer or name without disambiguation.
level_warning_multiple_singleton = Found { $count } "{ $name }" objects. The original game uses singleton-like scene lookups for this object and may pick an arbitrary instance or break when multiple exist.
level_warning_missing_level_manager = No "{ $name }" object was found. Many original-game systems dereference LevelManager directly, so preview/exported gameplay may break immediately.
level_warning_missing_level_start = No "{ $name }" object was found. The original game falls back to a default origin for contraption placement and camera setup, which can produce broken level behavior.
level_warning_missing_camera_system = No "{ $name }" object was found. The original game expects CameraSystem to create GameCamera and HUDCamera, then resolves cameras through singular lookups such as Camera.main and HUDCamera.
level_warning_missing_world_object = No "{ $name }" was found. LevelManager looks up a single World-tagged background object during load and immediately reads its PositionSerializer or name.
level_warning_missing_goal_area = No goal object matching "{ $name }" was found. In non-sandbox levels the original game resolves a single Goal-tagged target for completion, so finishing the level may be impossible.
level_warning_multiple_goal_area = Found { $count } goal objects matching "{ $name }". LevelManager resolves the goal through a single Goal-tag lookup and may use an arbitrary one when multiple goal areas exist.
level_warning_missing_dessert_places = No "{ $name }" object was found. Shipped levels consistently include this root, but BaseGameMode soft-skips dessert placement when it is missing, so dessert spawning may be disabled instead of crashing.
level_warning_multiple_dessert_places = Found { $count } "{ $name }" objects. BaseGameMode resolves a single DessertPlaces root through GameObject.Find("DessertPlaces"), so multiple roots can make dessert placement load from an arbitrary branch.
level_warning_continue = Continue anyway?

